# CLAUDE.local.md — example

Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` and edit for your environment. `CLAUDE.local.md` is auto-gitignored by Claude Code; canonical/shared instructions belong in `CLAUDE.md` instead.

Everything below is user-, platform-, or preference-specific and does **not** generalize across users.

---

## Environment

<!-- YOUR local Python / shell setup. The example below is one author's Windows + conda configuration — replace with yours. -->

### Running Python

The `Bash` tool uses bash, not PowerShell, so conda activation doesn't work directly. To run Python scripts inside the `work-buddy` conda env on Windows:

```
powershell.exe -Command "cd <repo-root>; conda activate work-buddy; <your command here>"
```

If you use a different shell / env manager (venv, pyenv, direnv, etc.), document your activation pattern here so any dev agent working in your environment uses the right Python.

### Dependency management

`work-buddy` uses **Poetry** — that part is canonical and lives in `CLAUDE.md`. What's local to you is which Poetry workflow you actually use:

- Production deps: `poetry add <package>`
- Temporary / testing deps: `poetry add --group temp <package>` (cleanly removable later)
- Remove: `poetry remove <package>` or `poetry remove --group temp <package>`

